=Description=

"Where did Critical Social Justice come from? How did it get to a point where the Grievance Studies Affair was possible? What’s the relevance of postmodernism? What about Neo-Marxism and Critical Theory in all of this? How does it think, why does it think that way, and where is it going? Is it a reflexive movement, and what does that mean? Most importantly, what can people do about it?

Join James Lindsay as he sits down on the Agora Politics podcast to discuss these issues and why he created New Discourses to help people better understand them."

